If I don't get what I want from someone, I look elsewhere. Which is really terrible. The end.

It is utterly amazing how simple it is to sever the mind-body connection...to the point that it feels like all of the commands your brain is giving your body are in Portuguese, and your body only vaguely understands French, so this really does no good.

Your body might recognize that your brain is actually singing Starman by David Bowie as covered by Seu Jorge (in Portuguese) so your body can at least hum along, but this may make the separation between mind             and                 body even more severe because you know all of the words in English but you can't, for the life of you, wrap your tongue around the tantalizing, teasing gibberish Portuguese that your BRAIN is sending you.

So once you have successfully completed this schism [which is really no big feat...as stated above, it is quite simple], you will soon discover that the true challenge falls in the realm of trying to force your mindandbody to work together again. There will be many times that you will think you have accomplished this...getting high, a sunny day, going barefoot are the big tricksters, and perhaps they denote a smaller connection...but the cat's meow of mindbodysynthesis  is tears of joy. Really. When you find someone who has imperfections so perfectly arranged that they confuse both your body and mind so much that your happiness becomes sadness--you can't believe you are lucky enough to have this brilliant confusion-that is Bliss.

Unfortunately, this bliss is nearly impossible to find. It is ever harder to hold onto. Try pouring the ocean into a paper cup...

Tonight is my last night of an outrageously long vacation.

This vacation was so long, I don't even remember when it started anymore. I also don't quite remember everthing I did...I got a job (at Borders) spent too much money (mostly on records and at TJ MAXX), watched many films, CLEANED MY ROOM, drank lots of tea, flipped out a few times, etc etc etc...
the usual, I suppose.

I am in love with someone but trying to ignore it by filling my life with substitutes. so i spend my time excited and bored. and not quite fufilled. 
and nostaligic for my future-if that makes any sense. 


"one way or another, we all feel like we're the only ones."

"I am in pain because I fell in love with a person who doesn't want to be with me. Or, maybe (he) wants to, but (he) can't. I don't know. Does it matter? Beyond the tiniest distinctions in the chemistry of my ego, I don't think it really matters. It can't happen. I CAN'T GET WHAT I WANT.
Which is to go to sleep with (him) by my side, and wake up in the morning with (him) still there next to me, maybe holding my hand. I want to look into (his) face, and feel (him) letting me look into (him), and then, you know, I want to keep going on in. I want us to be able to go into each other, calmly, and quietly, without a lot of bullshit and built up hopes, and destroyed hopes. Destroyed homes. I want us to start a conversation that doesn't get interrupted. I want us both to be comfortable letting each other in, like a slowly rising body of water.
I want us to pour our liquids into the plastic pop bottle, and then shake it really hard and just hang on and see how it feels. Just imagining it feels amazing."
